      "content": "it just seems like you're saying the \"empirical\" side is the objective truth while the constitutional side is just a matter of principle or \"norms.\" if the data shows a law works to prevent death, isn't it basically a fact that the law is \"good,\" and anyone arguing against it on constitutional grounds is just prioritizing abstract theory over actual human lives?",
