      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While I acknowledge the compelling nature of data showing a law is effective in saving lives, it is not purely a matter of facts versus abstract theory. Constitutional law serves as the framework that ensures legislation aligns with the fundamental principles enshrined in a nation's founding documents. It offers protection against potential government overreach and safeguards individual rights, which can be crucial for democracy and civil liberties. Focusing only on the empirical results may inadvertently support short-term fixes without considering the long-term implications and protections intended by the constitution. Thus, both empirical evidence and constitutional integrity are vital to the health of a society.",
